titlestmt.titleproper: A Guide to the Mary M. Kritz papers FA269

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2016-08-22 23:37:52 -0400.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open for scholarly research.

RAC is unable to provide access to obsolete media and original digital media. In addition separated media may not yet have undergone stabilization procedures. When feasible, a digital surrogate may be created via special order. All applicable charges will apply. See RAC Head of Archival Services or RAC Head of Digital Programs for details.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Rockefeller Archive Center holds title, copyright and literary rights in the collection, in so far as it holds them, and has authority to grant permission to cite and publish archival material from the collection.

phystech.head: Physical Characteristics and Technical Requirements
phystech.p: Materials requiring specialized equipment for access (film, audio, video, slides) may be closed to research dependent on availability of the applicable equipment
Brittle or damaged items, or materials otherwise in need of preservation care, may be closed to researchers at the discretion of the RAC Head of Archival Services/Head of Reference.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The files were received by the Rockefeller Archive Center, from Mary M. Kritz, in 2000 and were officially ingeted as Accession 2000:039.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Preliminary archival processing of the Kritz papers was conducted by the Rockefeller Archive Center to establish intellectual and physical control of the material and assess its immediate preservation and conservation needs. The collection remains in storage boxes and in original folders. Further archival processing, primarily to facilitate the long-term preservation of the records will be conducted at a later date, as necessary.
The finding aid was prepared by Diane April, May 2012; with front matter notes contributed by Robert Battaly, RAC Head of Processing.
